<recipe>
<title>
Cranberry Balsamic Pork Tenderloin
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 5 minutes
COOK TIME: 15 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 20 minutes
</details>
<ingredients>
1 1/2 c. cranberry pineapple 100% juice*
1/4 c. lite soy sauce
1/4 c. balsamic vinegar
1/4 c. brown sugar, packed
1 1/2 T. cornstarch
1 1/2 c. fresh cranberries
1 Smithfield Marinated Sweet Teriyaki Pork Tenderloin
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 400 F.
Stir together juice, soy sauce, balsamic vinegar, brown sugar, and cornstarch until combined. 
Add pork tenderloin to large, oven-safe skillet.
Pour juice mixture into skillet, and add cranberries.
Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until meat registers 145F.
Let rest for 10 minutes before slicing. 
Spoon sauce over meat to serve.
</instructions>
</recipe>
